<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f99546185345707>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Post 50 Wizard are Gods</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jul 18th 9:10 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=52948><span id= >Themasterfizzler</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>There is a false rumor going around that casters should not nuke until a mob is down to 50% or so. Sometime that can be 70% with higher level mobs. This statement is from the countless numbers of uninformed PCs who don't know the Wizards real abilities. <br>Apart from the fast nukes, snares, roots, stuns, and new Translocating (what a money maker), the wizard is given a quest called Brain Bite/Concussion. This spell effectively places the wizard on the bottom of the mobs hate list everytime that it is cast. It costs 75mana has an instant recast and a fast cast time.<br><br>Why is this important? Many times on high level raids with more than one group, unless you are in the prime group you will get no exp. With a few wizards in your group this will not happen. High level enchanters are a necessity on any raid so we assume that CII or better is always available and Tashani is cast on all mobs.<br><br>A well trained Wizard need not wait for 70% or 50% damage to nuke or cast. With a 658 nuke and an 1800 or better rain spell, the wizard can cast from start to finish alternating every 2 nukes or 2 rain waves with the brain bite. Even throwing in stuns from time to time if they wish. (stuns are high aggro if you try to sit afterwards). So basically a wizard can unload their worst damage on a mob and never fear being aggroed or summouned. Kind of like Fire and Forget. The Brain Bite is resistable and sometimes must be recast to make it stick. Once it does the wizard can sit and med at their leisure. <br><br>On a recent day I spent 20 straight hours in Hate and POG. I was able to help my group gain experience 1 out of 3 mobs, and I had a chanter, mage, druid, cleric in my group. IN a group of 4 we were outdamaging a 60 tank, 58 and 56 necros, 55 ranger, 53 Bard, and 58 cleric. And the majority of the major damage comes from the Wizard. I was summouned 3 times all day and aggroed once when i attempted to sit after not sticking the brain bite spell.<br><br>True in very long battles the wizard is not the major damage dealer, but with mobs up to about 30k HP(90% of mobs) the wizard can make the difference. <br><br>This is the standard operation in controlled raids, where I help my group make valuable experience over an extended period. I would much rather make a few bars of exp over all that time than nothing.<br><br>Adding just one more wizard to the group and your group will get 80% of the experience. Tanks don't know about this and don't want anyone too otherwise you can steal their thunder.<br>If your a wizard in this situation, try this and sit back and laugh as you effectively outdamage 6 other PCs. The necro are the only other PC that can do fast damage with pets and dots so pick your mobs wisely.<br><br>And yes this spell works on all mobs with lowered MR, even level 60 plus. The cost of the spell is negligable when you get over 3000 mana.&nbsp;&nbsp;CII regens mana so fast that this chain nuking does not keep you out of the fight for long. <br><br>More people would appreciate the wizard if they understood its abilities.<br><br>Khadgars Arkimist<br>54 Wizard - Fennin Ro<br>"Fear my wrath"</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
